      "agentResultText": "Build passes. Here's a summary of everything that was implemented:\n\n**Installed:** `@propelauth/nextjs`\n\n**New files created:**\n- `src/app/api/auth/[slug]/route.ts` — PropelAuth route handler for login/logout/callback flows, redirects to `/dashboard` after login\n- `src/middleware.ts` — Auth middleware that processes auth tokens on all routes\n- `src/lib/auth.ts` — Helper that calls `getUserOrRedirect()` and upserts the PropelAuth user into the local Prisma DB\n- `src/components/auth-buttons.tsx` — Client component showing login/signup buttons when logged out, email + logout when logged in\n\n**Modified files:**\n- `prisma/schema.prisma` — Added `propelAuthId` (String, unique, optional) to the User model\n- `src/app/layout.tsx` — Wrapped with `AuthProvider`, added `AuthButtons` to the navbar\n- `src/app/dashboard/page.tsx` — Uses `getAuthUser()` to fetch the authenticated user, scopes posts to that user\n- `src/app/dashboard/actions.ts` — All actions (create/update/delete) use `getAuthUser()` instead of `DEFAULT_USER_ID`, and update/delete are scoped to `authorId`\n- `src/app/settings/page.tsx` — Uses `getAuthUser()` instead of hardcoded user ID\n- `src/app/settings/actions.ts` — Uses `getAuthUser()` instead of `DEFAULT_USER_ID`\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Unauthenticated users can visit the home page freely\n2. Visiting `/dashboard` or `/settings` triggers `getUserOrRedirect()` which redirects to PropelAuth's hosted login page\n3. After login, the callback redirects to `/dashboard`\n4. The `getAuthUser()` helper auto-creates a local DB user on first login (matched by `propelAuthId`)\n5. All data operations are scoped to the authenticated user",
